---
// Static SVG: Circle with both an outer square (side 2r) and an inner square (rotated 45°,
// corners touching the circle). Shows the Pythagoras construction and the bound 2 < π < 4.
---

<figure class="diagram">
  <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100%" viewBox="0 0 500 430" aria-label="Circle with inscribed and circumscribed squares, showing the Pythagoras construction for bounding pi" role="img">

    <!-- Outer square -->
    <rect x="130" y="60" width="240" height="240" fill="none" stroke="#555" stroke-width="2"/>

    <!-- Circle -->
    <circle cx="250" cy="180" r="120" fill="none" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="2"/>

    <!-- Inner square (rotated 45°) -->
    <polygon points="250,60 370,180 250,300 130,180" fill="#6366f1" opacity="0.08" stroke="#d63030" stroke-width="2"/>

    <!-- Centre dot -->
    <circle cx="250" cy="180" r="3" fill="#555"/>

    <!-- Radius line from centre to right corner of inner square -->
    <line x1="250" y1="180" x2="370" y2="180" stroke="#6366f1" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="6,4"/>
    <text x="310" y="172" font-size="14" fill="#6366f1" text-anchor="middle" font-family="serif" font-style="italic">r</text>

    <!-- Pythagoras construction: centre → top corner (vertical) and centre → right corner (horizontal) -->
    <line x1="250" y1="180" x2="370" y2="180" stroke="#aaa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
    <line x1="370" y1="180" x2="250" y2="60" stroke="#aaa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>

    <!-- Vertical line from centre to top corner = r -->
    <line x1="250" y1="180" x2="250" y2="60" stroke="#d63030" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="5,4"/>
    <text x="237" y="125" font-size="13" fill="#d63030" text-anchor="end" font-family="serif" font-style="italic">r</text>

    <!-- Inner square side label: r√2 -->
    <text x="325" y="108" font-size="13" fill="#d63030" text-anchor="start" font-family="serif" font-style="italic">r&#x221A;2</text>

    <!-- Right angle marker at centre -->
    <rect x="250" y="168" width="12" height="12" fill="none" stroke="#aaa" stroke-width="1"/>

    <!-- Corner dots where inner square meets circle -->
    <circle cx="250" cy="60" r="4" fill="#d63030"/>
    <circle cx="370" cy="180" r="4" fill="#d63030"/>
    <circle cx="250" cy="300" r="4" fill="#d63030"/>
    <circle cx="130" cy="180" r="4" fill="#d63030"/>

    <!-- Labels for each square -->
    <text x="138" y="54" font-size="12" fill="#555" font-family="sans-serif">Outer square: area = 4<tspan font-style="italic">r</tspan><tspan font-size="9" dy="-4">2</tspan></text>
    <text x="250" y="400" font-size="12" fill="#d63030" text-anchor="middle" font-family="sans-serif"><tspan dy="0">Inner square: area = 2</tspan><tspan font-style="italic">r</tspan><tspan font-size="9" dy="-4">2</tspan></text>

    <!-- Summary bound -->
    <text x="250" y="420" font-size="14" fill="#333" text-anchor="middle" font-family="sans-serif">2 &lt; <tspan font-style="italic">&pi;</tspan> &lt; 4</text>

  </svg>
  <figcaption>A circle of radius r sandwiched between two squares. The outer square (grey) has area 4r². The inner square (red, rotated 45°) has area 2r². The circle's area is somewhere in between, so 2 &lt; &pi; &lt; 4.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .diagram {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .diagram svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 420px;
    height: auto;
    margin: 0 auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .diagram figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
